main event: Unidentified objects detected on radar and visually observed over Key West, Florida on November 14 and 15, 1950.
interesting points: On November 14, 1950, an unidentified aircraft was picked up on ground radar, traveling at around 450 mph at an altitude of 15,000 feet. It made a turn to the right and faded from the radar scope.
A flight of PGF-5N aircraft attempted to visually intercept the unidentified target, but were unable to make visual contact.

On November 15, 1950, another unidentified aircraft was detected on ground radar at 15,000 feet, with an estimated speed more than twice as fast as the PGF-5N fighters which were cruising at 460 knots.
One experienced VF(N) pilot was able to make a visual sighting of the unidentified aircraft, describing it as having a long silver fuselage with no lights.
The radar contacts and visual sightings occurred in a designated warning area, and no known military aircraft were scheduled to be operating in the area at those times.
